MBOMBELA &#8211; Divergent Ops responded to a call today from a member of the public who had seen the mortar bomb.According to the security company&#8217;s Mr Jacques Meiring, the bomb squad was called out and removed the mortar shell from the scene.&#8220;There is no cause for alarm as it was found to be a practice mortar bomb,&#8221; he said.The road is open as usual.For your interest Dictionary.com says a mortar is &#8220;a cannon very short in proportion to its bore, for throwing shells at high angles&#8221;.Also read: UPDATE: Police rescue man off hospital roof